PART 4: e AS GROWTH вЂ” EXPONENTIAL STRUCTURE
======================================================================

  How does e appear in tournament theory?

  1. TOURNAMENT COUNT: 2^{C(n,2)} tournaments on n vertices.
     logв‚‚(count) = n(n-1)/2. So count = e^{n(n-1)ln(2)/2}.
     The base-e growth rate of tournament space is ln(2)В·nВІ/2.

  2. HAMILTONIAN PATH ASYMPTOTICS: E[H] = n!/2^{n-1}.
     By Stirling: n! ~ в€љ(2ПЂn)В·(n/e)^n.
     So E[H] ~ в€љ(2ПЂn)В·(n/e)^n / 2^{n-1} = в€љ(2ПЂn)В·(n/(2e))^n В· 2.
     The ratio n/(2e) determines whether H grows or shrinks.
     Critical n: 2e в‰€ 5.44. For n в‰Ґ 6, E[H] grows superexponentially.

  3. INDEPENDENCE POLYNOMIAL: I(О©, e) is a natural evaluation.
     The "e-count" of a tournament: I(О©, e) = 1 + cв‚ѓВ·e + О±в‚‚В·eВІ + ...
     This weights cycle packings by e^{size}, connecting to EGF.

  4. EXPONENTIAL GENERATING FUNCTION of H:
     ОЈ_{nв‰Ґ1} E[H(n)] x^n / n! = ОЈ x^n / 2^{n-1} = 2x/(2-x) = 2/(2/x - 1)
     Singularity at x = 2. Radius of convergence = 2. Again: 2.

