PART 8: THE MГ–BIUS STRIP вЂ” NON-ORIENTABILITY OF H-GRADIENT
======================================================================

  S71v proved: в€‡H(T^op) = -в€‡H(T).
  The gradient is a SECTION of the MГ¶bius bundle over T/{complement}.

  Now we make this precise using the SIGN CHARACTER:
    Оµ: (Z/2)^m в†’ {В±1}, Оµ(Пѓ) = (-1)^{|Пѓ|}

  where |Пѓ| = number of arcs flipped.

  The tournament space {0,1}^m has the DOUBLE COVER:
    {0,1}^m Г— {В±1} в†’ {0,1}^m
  where the Z/2 action is: ПѓВ·(T, s) = (T^op, -s).

  The MГ¶bius bundle is the quotient by this action.
  A SECTION of the MГ¶bius bundle is a function f satisfying:
    f(T^op) = -f(T)

  в€‡H is such a section. But there are others:
    - S(T) at odd n (the signed permanent)
    - Any odd-degree Walsh component of H
    - The SIGN of any asymmetric invariant

  The MГ¶bius strip appears because the complement involution
  has NO FIXED POINTS (no self-complementary tournament exists
  when n в‰Ў 2,3 mod 4). When fixed points exist (n в‰Ў 0,1 mod 4),
  the bundle is TRIVIALIZABLE at those points.

  This connects to the FIRST STIEFEL-WHITNEY CLASS:
    wв‚Ѓ в€€ HВ№(T/Zв‚‚; Z/2)
  which classifies the MГ¶bius bundle up to isomorphism.
  wв‚Ѓ в‰  0 iff the bundle is NON-TRIVIAL iff the complement
  involution acts freely (no self-complementary tournaments).

  Self-complementary tournament existence:
    n=3: 8 self-complementary, SC exists: YES (bundle trivializable)
    n=4: 48 self-complementary, SC exists: YES (bundle trivializable)
    n=5: 704 self-complementary, SC exists: YES (bundle trivializable)
    n=6: 0 self-complementary (6 в‰Ў 2 mod 4), SC exists: NO (MГ¶bius non-trivial)
    n=7: 456 self-complementary (7 в‰Ў 3 mod 4), SC exists: YES (bundle trivializable)
    SC exists iff n в‰Ў 0 or 1 mod 4 (Moon's criterion)
    But n=3: SC exists (3 в‰Ў 3 mod 4!) вЂ” the 3-cycle IS self-complementary

