PART 11: 2 AND 7 IN THE LIGHT OF e^{iПЂ} = -1
======================================================================

  e^{iПЂ} = -1. The RIGHT side has order 2 in C*.
  e^{iВ·2ПЂ/7} = О¶в‚‡, a primitive 7th root of unity.

  The RELATIONSHIP between -1 and О¶в‚‡:
    (-1)^{7/2} is not defined in R.
    But in C: (-1)^{7/2} = e^{iВ·7ПЂ/2} = e^{iВ·3ПЂ/2 + iВ·2ПЂ} = e^{iВ·3ПЂ/2} = -i.
    So (-1)^{7/2} = -i. The half-integer power connects 2 and 7 through i!

  More: О¶в‚‡Ві + О¶в‚‡ВІ + О¶в‚‡ + 1 + О¶в‚‡вЃ»В№ + О¶в‚‡вЃ»ВІ + О¶в‚‡вЃ»Ві = 0
  (sum of all 7th roots = 0)

  The GAUSS SUM: g = ОЈ_{aв€€F_7*} (a/7)В·О¶в‚‡^a
  where (a/7) is the Legendre symbol.
  gВІ = (-1)^{(7-1)/2} В· 7 = (-1)Ві В· 7 = -7.
  So g = iв€љ7. The Gauss sum connects i, 7, and the Legendre symbol.

  For F_7: QR = {1, 2, 4}, NR = {3, 5, 6}.
  The Paley tournament on 7 vertices: aв†’b iff (b-a) в€€ QR.
  Its EIGENVALUES involve (-1 В± iв€љ7)/2 вЂ” exactly the Gauss sum!

  So the Paley tournament P_7 carries Euler's identity in its spectrum:
    eigenvalues = (n-1)/2 (once), (-1 В± iв€љ7)/2 (each three times)

  The eigenvalue (-1+iв€љ7)/2 has:
    |(-1+iв€љ7)/2|ВІ = (1+7)/4 = 2.
    MODULUS = в€љ2.

  The number 2 appears as the SQUARED MODULUS of the Paley eigenvalue!
  This is WHY we evaluate I(О©, x) at x = 2.

  Paley tournament P_7 eigenvalues:
    eigenvalues: 3.0000  -0.5000+1.3229i  -0.5000+1.3229i  -0.5000-1.3229i  -0.5000-1.3229i  -0.5000+1.3229i  -0.5000-1.3229i  
    |-0.5000-1.3229i|ВІ = 2.0001
    |-0.5000+1.3229i|ВІ = 2.0001
    |3.0000+0.0000i|ВІ = 9.0000

  Gauss sum g = ОЈ (a/7)В·О¶в‚‡^a:
    g = 0.000000 + 2.645751i
    gВІ = -7.000000 + 0.000000i
    Expected: gВІ = -7 = -7
    |g|ВІ = 7.000000 = 7

