PART 12: THE GOLDEN CIRCLE вЂ” П„ MEETS ПЂ IN THE PENTAGON
======================================================================

  The regular pentagon unifies П„ and ПЂ:
    cos(2ПЂ/5) = (П„-1)/2 = (в€љ5-1)/4
    cos(ПЂ/5) = П„/2
    cos(4ПЂ/5) = -П„/2
    2В·cos(2ПЂ/5) = П„-1 = 1/П„

  The DIAGONAL-TO-SIDE ratio of the regular pentagon = П„.
  This is a GEOMETRIC fact connecting ПЂ (circle в†’ polygon) to П„ (proportion).

  In tournament theory:
    Cв‚… (cyclic tournament on 5) has eigenvalues involving П„.
    The regular pentagon = the Cayley graph of Z/5 with generators {1,2}.
    This IS Cв‚… (since QR mod 5 = {1,4} and NR = {2,3}, but the
    DIRECTED structure depends on QR choice).

  The golden ratio in I(О©, П„):
    I(О©, П„) = a + bВ·П„ в€€ Z[П„] = ring of integers of Q(в€љ5).
    The NORM: N(a+bП„) = aВІ + ab - bВІ.
    The UNIT GROUP: Z[П„]* = {В±П„^n : n в€€ Z}.
    Units have norm В±1. So N = В±1 iff I(О©,П„) is a UNIT.

  Is I(О©,П„) ever a unit? Check:

  I(О©,П„) norm analysis at n=5:
    H=  1: I = 1 + 0П„, N = 1, I(П„) = 1.000000 UNIT!
