VERIFICATION: PALEY EIGENVALUE MODULUSВІ = 2
======================================================================
  For Paley tournament P_p (p в‰Ў 3 mod 4):
  Eigenvalue modulusВІ = (1+p)/4

    p=  3: |eig|ВІ = (1+3)/4 = 1.0  в†ђ THIS IS 1!
    p=  7: |eig|ВІ = (1+7)/4 = 2.0  в†ђ THIS IS 2!
    p= 11: |eig|ВІ = (1+11)/4 = 3.0  в†ђ THIS IS 3!
    p= 19: |eig|ВІ = (1+19)/4 = 5.0  в†ђ THIS IS 5!
    p= 23: |eig|ВІ = (1+23)/4 = 6.0  в†ђ THIS IS 6!
    p= 31: |eig|ВІ = (1+31)/4 = 8.0  в†ђ THIS IS 8!
    p= 43: |eig|ВІ = (1+43)/4 = 11.0  в†ђ THIS IS 11!
    p= 47: |eig|ВІ = (1+47)/4 = 12.0  в†ђ THIS IS 12!
    p= 59: |eig|ВІ = (1+59)/4 = 15.0  в†ђ THIS IS 15!
    p= 67: |eig|ВІ = (1+67)/4 = 17.0  в†ђ THIS IS 17!
    p= 71: |eig|ВІ = (1+71)/4 = 18.0  в†ђ THIS IS 18!
    p= 79: |eig|ВІ = (1+79)/4 = 20.0  в†ђ THIS IS 20!
    p= 83: |eig|ВІ = (1+83)/4 = 21.0  в†ђ THIS IS 21!

  The primes p where |Paley eigenvalue|ВІ is an INTEGER:
  (1+p)/4 в€€ Z вџє p в‰Ў 3 mod 4 (always true for Paley) AND 1+p в‰Ў 0 mod 4 вџє p в‰Ў 3 mod 4 вњ“
  So |eig|ВІ = (p+1)/4 is ALWAYS an integer for Paley!

  The sequence: p=3в†’1, p=7в†’2, p=11в†’3, p=19в†’5, p=23в†’6, p=31в†’8, ...
  These are the values (p+1)/4 for p в‰Ў 3 mod 4.

  AT p=7: |eig|ВІ = 2. The evaluation point.
  AT p=3: |eig|ВІ = 1. The multiplicative identity.
  AT p=71: |eig|ВІ = 18 = 2В·3ВІ (session number S71!)

  p=7 is the UNIQUE prime where Paley eigenvalue modulusВІ = 2.
  This is WHY 7 is special: it's the prime that makes
  the spectral evaluation point equal to the OCF evaluation point.

